Each and every server was polite, kind and patient- and this is no small feat when serving a group of teens! Huge shout out to the staff here- we will be back.

reviews.review_text: Ordered food by calling, while we assumed White Spot could deliver to curbside according to information on Google Maps. Turns out the information is inaccurate so there is NO CURBSIDE PICKUP. However, all other routes (delivery, sit-in, and walk-in pick-up) are available. Bless the workers on shift today, they were okay to make an exception and still let us do curbside pickup. For anyone reading this, please know this was just an exception, dont expect them to do this unless you ask and theyre ok to do it. Food was 10/10 so people can be confident that theres no going wrong with White Spot on Dunsmuir St.

Being from North Carolina we had no idea where to find a good traditional breakfast. Thankfully a bell man at our hotel mentioned White Spot. Sounded good so we headed out and are so glad we did. The restaurant is spacious, clean and pretty! We had the pleasure of having Sabine as our waitress. What a sweetheart!! Super informative about the restaurant and the surrounding area. Even had the manager and another associate to stop by to to answer some of our questions. The food was delicious and the best coffee I ve had in a few weeks. We plan to head back there every morning and possibly even for lunch or dinner while we re here!

- Henry s review. This is by far my favourite place throughout my trip to Canada and America. This was outstanding food and exceptional customer service. It is a very well organised restaurant and I felt comfortable and safe throughout the restaurant. Even the bathrooms were nice unlike most places. When I tried Popeyes chicken sandwich I thought that was great, but this was beyond exceptional and both me and my taste buds think that this food was better than anything I have tried before. I will be sure to recommend all my friends to this restaurant as they will love it as much, or more than me. Thanks, Henry!

Love love the burgers! the bottomless fries are the best. I always get the triple o sauce on the side for extra kick.  I highly recommend their Chicken Alfredo. Generous amount of chicken with creamy pasta. Always a great experience.

Waiter looked sketchy at first, but he did a bang up job and was exactly the sort of person I want attending. He knew when I wanted coffee two minutes before I knew I wanted more. The timing of his delivery was spot on. Would return again if I was in town for breakfast.

The staff is very professional. I enjoy the endless cups of coffee. The restaurant was very clean and quiet. Social distancing protocols were follow which is good, you wont get that at other restaurants. Good job staff

Went there on the hottest day and their ac really cool me down. :) Also a very clean and tidy dining area. The food was good and better than some other Vancouver White Spot locations. Friendly customer services.   Will come back again!

I dine at this location about 5 or 6 times a month and enjoy the food and atmosphere greatly, the food is always excelent and if you are like me, always thirsty theres no problem with that because if you are having a soft drink with your meal your glass is never empty, and that leaves the staff, the wait staff is far the best and im conpairing it to other places i dine, like earls dt and global as well, hands down the whitespot on dunsmier has the best wait staff and their cooks are not to be recon with as well. The food is always hot and the portions are alway generous, in most restaraunts i will tip 15 percent even if the serves is medeoker but i will admit when i leave the spot rarely do i ever leave under 30 percent and even have left as high as 75 percent and feel it was deserved, i rate this a 10 out of ten with a 11 out of 10 on the staff.

This helps a lot when you re trying to avoid non-vegan food. The vegan food they do have is excellent   I love the sweetcorn mix they place at the bottom of their beyond burger, and my spouse thinks their gherkins are the tastiest gherkins ever.
